    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "QuantumScramblingSimulate[{a, b}, {p, t}, {s1, s2, ...}] classically \
simulates the quantum information scrambling in random quantum circuits on \
qubits {s1, s Subscript[2, ], ...} in terms of the out-of-time-order \
correlator C(t) := \\[LeftAngleBracket]a^\\[Dagger] (t) b^\\[Dagger] a( t) \
b\\[RightAngleBracket], where a and b are local unitary operators. The random \
quantum circuit consists of random two-qubit unitary gates and random \
single-qubit measurements in the computational basis. The measurement is \
performed with probability p, and the circuit has depth t.", "synonyms" -> {},
